          <td class="NewsTitleDescription" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">M'lady Robech's wonderful idea, here goes...<br>
          <br></td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">We shall all start a new character on a new server and have about 2 or 3 hours to get ourselves levelled and at least a little learned in our new roles. <br><br>The server and teams will not be anounced until the day of the event. We will meet in the Arena in Lake Rathe on our Main characters for the announcement of the the server, teams, and location to meet once on the alt-server. We will then all log and head to said server, create a brand new character <b>THAT YOU HAVE LITTLE OR NO EXPERIENCE WITH</b>. Then group up with your team and begin learning about your new character and gain as much XP and items as you can in the alloted amount of time. Once the time is up, we shall all meet at a PVP type area where we will then conduct a tournament between the teams to see who learned the most about the characters and teamwork.<br><br>When all is said and done and we have our victors, we will then come back to Rodcet on your Mains again where I will try to have some prizes for the winning team and then we can brawl or drink (or both for Durgin).<br><br>This gives us all a great opportunity to learn about new characters, the players BEHIND the characters in our guild, and combining teamwork with having fun. <br><br>So if you have a sense of adventure and want some great fun, which I know you all do, then join Robech and I and your other guildmates on this joyride!!<br><br><br>And you thought I was a tank before... hehehe!!<br>
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
